#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
netmon.py — live network status dashboard for the rover / station rig.

Pings every device in parallel and shows a colour-coded, grouped table that
refreshes on an interval. Latency is shown in ms, and any state change
(device dropping or recovering) is appended to a log file.

Requires: rich   ->   pip install rich

Examples:
    ./netmon.py                       # live dashboard, 2s refresh
    ./netmon.py -i 5                  # refresh every 5 seconds
    ./netmon.py --once                # single snapshot then exit
    ./netmon.py --log /var/log/netmon.log
"""

